TWO suspects have escaped while they were being transported from Burgersfort Regional Court to Leboeng Police Station, Limpopo police said. David Ramahlo, 30, and Moses Ngwatle, 39, escaped after their appearance in court on housebreaking and theft charges, police spokesman Lieutenant-Colonel Moatshe Ngoepe said."When the police car stopped at a robot in Burgersfort town the two suspects, who were handcuffed, opened the door, jumped out and disappeared.&rdquo;Police would investigate the circumstances around the incident, Ngoepe said.Anyone with information that can lead to the re-arrest of the two escapers can contact Crime Stop at 0860010111 or SMS the crime line on 32211.